<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">April 28, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-april-28-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-252992 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The_Kitchen_circa_1934_looking_northeast-150x150.jpg" alt="kitchen" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.eater.com/24413816/cookbook-advice-chefs-bartenders-clarkson-potter" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">What does it take to write a cookbook?</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://thebaffler.com/latest/heteropessimism-of-the-intellect-isack?utm_source%3Drss-feed%26utm_medium%3Drss%26utm_campaign%3Dfeed" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The heteropessimism of Sophie Kemp’s fiction</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/books/a64452881/shakespeare-at-40-may-2025/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mitchell S. Jackson reads Shakespeare for the first time in his 40s</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-april-28-2025/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
